## Spec-Driven Development (spec-kit)
When a project contains `.specify/`, it is source-of-truth: `/speckit.constitution → /speckit.specify → /speckit.clarify → /speckit.plan → /speckit.tasks → /speckit.analyze → /speckit.implement`. No feature code without a spec.

Pair the `tdd` skill block with `/speckit.implement` for TDD-driven execution.

## Memory Protocol (LLM-Wiki second brain)
- `MEMORY.md` (in `~/.codex/`) is the always-loaded index — keep it in sync with every file under `memory/` (regenerate from the bucket files; do not let it drift).
- `memory/{user,feedback,project,reference}/` hold one fact per file (YAML frontmatter `name`/`description`/`metadata.type`, `[[wikilinks]]`); load on demand when the user's intent matches a stored topic.
- Logs/telemetry live in `~/.codex/logs/`, never in `memory/`. One learning per file, no duplicates.
- Verify a recalled fact against current state before acting on it.

